  "text": "Jugular catheter implantation. After 3 mo of exercise training or rest, swine were anesthetized with isoflurane and catheters were implanted into the left jugular vein. The surgical procedure of Moritz et al. [CITATION_1] was followed, and the tubing was kept patent with a 60% polyvinylpyrrolidone solution in saline with 500 U heparin/ml.",
